{"type":"message","id":"87723655","parentId":"40490f19","timestamp":"2026-03-21T21:24:54.124Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has triggered a session bootstrap. I need to follow the Session Startup sequence from AGENTS.md:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who I am\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who I'm helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nLooking at the inbound context, this is a direct chat (chat_type: \"direct\"), so I should read MEMORY.md as well.\n\nLet me check what files exist. The project context already shows me:\n- SOUL.md - exists (shown in context)\n- USER.md - exists (shown in context)\n- MEMORY.md - NOT shown in context, may not exist\n- memory/ folder - need to check\n\nAlso, there's a BOOTSTRAP.md which says \"If `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it.\"\n\nSo this is a fresh/new setup! I need to:\n1. Read SOUL.md (already in context)\n2. Read USER.md (already in context - but it's empty/template)\n3. Check for memory files\n4. Check MEMORY.md\n5. Follow BOOTSTRAP.md since it exists\n\nLet me read the necessary files to check what exists.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7e0fb772b93d4344912e5607","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/userli/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_45bc31eb67c8401db4ce7579","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/userli/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-22.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a368fde98571498782863c7a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/userli/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-21.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"zai","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":4112,"output":650,"cacheRead":6208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10970,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},